methods.isResolvable:
Returns true if the resolver can resolve the uri.

:param uri: (java.net.URI) - the uri
:return: (boolean) true if this resolver can resolve uri
methods.resolve:
Resolve uri into an object.

*Overload 1*  
  :param uri: (java.net.URI) - the URI
  :return: (java.lang.Object) the object
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param uri: io.deephaven.uri.ApplicationUri
  :return: io.deephaven.appmode.Field<java.lang.Object>
  
*Overload 3*  
  :param applicationId: java.lang.String
  :param fieldName: java.lang.String
  :return: io.deephaven.appmode.Field<java.lang.Object>

text:
The application table resolver is able to resolve application URIs.

 
 For example, dh:///app/my_app/field/my_field.
